{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Foundation Models framework lets you tap into the on-device large models at"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the core of Apple Intelligence. You can enhance your app by using generative"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"models to create content or perform tasks. The framework supports language"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"understanding and generation based on model capabilities."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For design guidance, see Human Interface Guidelines > Technologies > "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/generative-ai","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Understand-model-capabilities","level":2,"text":"Understand model capabilities"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When considering features for your app, it helps to know what the on-device"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"language model can do. The on-device model supports text generation and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"understanding that you can use to:"}]},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Capability","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompt example"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Summarize"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"“Summarize this article.”","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Extract entities"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“List the people and places mentioned in this text.”"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Understand text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"“What happens to the dog in this story?”","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Refine or edit text","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Change this story to be in second person.”"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Classify or judge text","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"“Is this text relevant to the topic ‘Swift’?”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Compose creative writing"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Generate a short bedtime story about a fox.”"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Generate tags from text","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Provide two tags that describe the main topics of this text.”"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Generate game dialog"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"“Respond in the voice of a friendly inn keeper.”","type":"text"}]}]]],"header":"row"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The on-device language model may not be suitable for handling all requests, like:"}]},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Capabilities to avoid"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompt example"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Do basic math"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"“How many b’s are there in bagel?”","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create code"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Generate a Swift navigation list.”"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Perform logical reasoning"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“If I’m at Apple Park facing Canada, what direction is Texas?”"}]}]]]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The model can complete complex generative tasks when you use guided generation or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tool calling. For more on handling complex tasks, or tasks that require extensive"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"world-knowledge, see "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/generating-swift-data-structures-with-guided-generation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/expanding-generation-with-tool-calling","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Check for availability","anchor":"Check-for-availability","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Before you use the on-device model in your app, check that the model is available","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"by creating an instance of ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel"},{"text":" with the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/default","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"property.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Model availability depends on device factors like:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The device must support Apple Intelligence.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The device must have Apple Intelligence turned on in Settings.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It can take some time for the model to download and become available when"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a person turns on Apple Intelligence.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Always verify model availability first, and plan for a fallback experience in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"case the model is unavailable."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct GenerativeView: View {","    // Create a reference to the system language model.","    private var model = SystemLanguageModel.default","","    var body: some View {","        switch model.availability {","        case .available:","            // Show your intelligence UI.","        case .unavailable(.deviceNotEligible):","            // Show an alternative UI.","        case .unavailable(.appleIntelligenceNotEnabled):","            // Ask the person to turn on Apple Intelligence.","        case .unavailable(.modelNotReady):","            // The model isn't ready because it's downloading or because of other system reasons.","        case .unavailable(let other):","            // The model is unavailable for an unknown reason.","        }","    }","}"]},{"text":"Create a session","anchor":"Create-a-session","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"After confirming that the model is available, create a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"object to call the model. For a single-turn interaction, create a new session","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"each time you call the model:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["// Create a session with the system model.","let session = LanguageModelSession()"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For a multiturn interaction — where the model retains some knowledge of what","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it produced — reuse the same session each time you call the model.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Provide-a-prompt-to-the-model","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Provide a prompt to the model"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Prompt","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is an input that the model responds to. Prompt engineering is the art"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of designing high-quality prompts so that the model generates a best possible","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"response for the request you make. A prompt can be as short as “hello”, or as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"long as multiple paragraphs. The process of designing a prompt involves a lot of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"exploration to discover the best prompt, and involves optimizing prompt length"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and writing style."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When thinking about the prompt you want to use in your app, consider using","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"conversational language in the form of a question or command. For example,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"“What’s a good month to visit Paris?” or “Generate a food truck menu.”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Write prompts that focus on a single and specific task, like “Write a profile"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the dog breed Siberian Husky”. When a prompt is long and complicated, the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"model takes longer to respond, and may respond in unpredictable ways. If you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"have a complex generation task in mind, break the task down into a series of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specific prompts."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can refine your prompt by telling the model exactly how much content it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"should generate. A prompt like, “Write a profile for the dog breed Siberian"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Husky” often takes a long time to process as the model generates a full"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"multi-paragraph essay. If you specify “using three sentences”, it speeds up","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"processing and generates a concise summary. Use phrases like “in a single"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"sentence” or “in a few words” to shorten the generation time and produce shorter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text."}]},{"code":["// Generate a longer response for a specific command.","let simple = \"Write me a story about pears.\"","","// Quickly generate a concise response.","let quick = \"Write the profile for the dog breed Siberian Husky using three sentences.\""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"level":2,"text":"Provide instructions to the model","anchor":"Provide-instructions-to-the-model","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Instructions","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" help steer the model in a way that fits the use case of your app."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The model obeys prompts at a lower priority than the instructions you provide."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"When you provide instructions to the model, consider specifying details like:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"What the model’s role is; for example, “You are a mentor,” or “You are a movie","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"critic”.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"What the model should do, like “Help the person extract calendar events,” or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"“Help the person by recommending search suggestions”."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"What the style preferences are, like “Respond as briefly as possible”."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"What the possible safety measures are, like “Respond"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with ‘I can’t help with that’ if you’re asked to do something dangerous”.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use content you trust in instructions because the model follows them more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"closely than the prompt itself. When you initialize a session with instructions,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it affects all prompts the model responds to in that session. Instructions can","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"also include example responses to help steer the model. When you add examples to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"your prompt, you provide the model with a template that shows the model what a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"good response looks like.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Generate a response","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Generate-a-response"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To call the model with a prompt, call "},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession/respond(to:options:)-b2re","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"on your session. The response call is asynchronous because it may take a few"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"seconds for the on-device foundation model to generate the response."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let instructions = \"\"\"","    Suggest five related topics. Keep them concise (three to seven words) and make sure they \\","    build naturally from the person's topic.","    \"\"\"","","let session = LanguageModelSession(instructions: instructions)","","let prompt = \"Making homemade bread\"","let response = try await session.respond(to: prompt)"]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A session can only handle a single request at a time, and causes a runtime","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"error if you call it again before the previous request finishes. Check "},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession/isResponding","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to verify the session is done processing the previous request before sending a new one."}]}],"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Instead of working with raw string output from the model, the framework offers","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"guided generation to generate a custom Swift data structure you define. For more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about guided generation, see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/generating-swift-data-structures-with-guided-generation","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you make a request to the model, you can provide custom tools to help the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"model complete the request. If the model determines that a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Tool","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" can assist with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the request, the framework calls your ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Tool"},{"text":" to perform additional actions like","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"retrieving content from your local database. For more information about tool","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calling, see "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/expanding-generation-with-tool-calling","isActive":true}]},{"level":2,"text":"Consider context size limits per session","anchor":"Consider-context-size-limits-per-session","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"context window size"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" is a limit on how much data the model can process for a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"session instance. A token is a chunk of text the model processes, and the system"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"model supports up to 4,096 tokens. A single token corresponds to three or four","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"characters in languages like English, Spanish, or German, and one token per character"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in languages like Japanese, Chinese, or Korean. In a single session, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sum of all tokens in the instructions, all prompts, and all outputs count toward"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the context window size."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your session processes a large amount of tokens that exceed the context"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"window, the framework throws the error "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession/GenerationError/exceededContextWindowSize(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"When you encounter the error, start a new session and try shortening your prompts.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If you need to process a large amount of data that won’t fit in a single context","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"window limit, break your data into smaller chunks, process each chunk in a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"separate session, and then combine the results."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For more information on managing the context window size, see"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Technotes/tn3193-managing-the-on-device-foundation-model-s-context-window","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Tune generation options and optimize performance","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Tune-generation-options-and-optimize-performance"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To get the best results for your prompt, experiment with different generation","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"options. ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/GenerationOptions","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" affects the runtime parameters of the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"model, and you can customize them for every request you make.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["// Customize the temperature to increase creativity.","let options = GenerationOptions(temperature: 2.0)","","let session = LanguageModelSession()","","let prompt = \"Write me a story about coffee.\"","let response = try await session.respond(","    to: prompt,","    options: options",")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When you test apps that use the framework, use Xcode Instruments to understand","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"more about the requests you make, like the time it takes to perform a request. When","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you make a request, you can access the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Transcript"},{"type":"text","text":" entries that describe the actions"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the model takes during your "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/technologies","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels"],["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/technologies","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/UseCase"],["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/technologies","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/UseCase"],["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/technologies","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/UseCase"]]},"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Updates/FoundationModels","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/adding-intelligent-app-features-with-generative-models","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Essentials"}],"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"Generating content and performing tasks with Foundation Models","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Foundation Models"}],"images":[{"type":"card","identifier":"foundation-models-PageImage-card.png"}]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/generating-content-and-performing-tasks-with-foundation-models"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Enhance the experience in your app by prompting an on-device large language model."}],"variants":[{"paths":["/documentation/foundationmodels/generating-content-and-performing-tasks-with-foundation-models"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels":{"url":"/documentation/foundationmodels","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Perform tasks with the on-device model that specializes in language understanding, structured output, and tool calling."}],"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels","images":[{"identifier":"foundation-models-framework-landing-PageImage-card.png","type":"card"}],"title":"Foundation Models","type":"topic","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Tool":{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Tool","title":"Tool","url":"/documentation/foundationmodels/tool","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A tool that a model can call to gather information at runtime or perform side effects.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Tool"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Tool","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel":{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel","title":"SystemLanguageModel","abstract":[{"text":"An on-device large language model capable of text generation tasks.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SystemLanguageModel"}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SystemLanguageModel"}],"url":"/documentation/foundationmodels/systemlanguagemodel"},"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Transcript":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Transcript"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Transcript"}],"title":"Transcript","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A linear history of entries that reflect an interaction with a session.","type":"text"}],"url":"/documentation/foundationmodels/transcript","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Transcript"},"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/generating-swift-data-structures-with-guided-generation":{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/generating-swift-data-structures-with-guided-generation","url":"/documentation/foundationmodels/generating-swift-data-structures-with-guided-generation","kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create robust apps by describing output you want programmatically."}],"title":"Generating Swift data structures with guided generation"},"adding-intelligent-app-features-with-generative-models-PageImage-card.png":{"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"https://docs-assets.developer.apple.com/published/29399e54b8f238bef3b51af88ed97253/adding-intelligent-app-features-with-generative-models-PageImage-card%402x.png","traits":["2x","light"]},{"url":"https://docs-assets.developer.apple.com/published/5b6f36cef31dcb9443d08d1885d21cab/adding-intelligent-app-features-with-generative-models-PageImage-card~dark%402x.png","traits":["2x","dark"]}],"identifier":"adding-intelligent-app-features-with-generative-models-PageImage-card.png","alt":"A screenshot of an itinerary planning app."},"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession/respond(to:options:)-b2re":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"respond","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"to"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"options","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:16FoundationModels17GenerationOptionsV","text":"GenerationOptions"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"async","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:16FoundationModels20LanguageModelSessionC","text":"LanguageModelSession"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:16FoundationModels20LanguageModelSessionC8ResponseV","text":"Response","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"te